===Prelude===
After suffering betrayal and near imprisonment in [[Qarth]], Daenerys departed the city on a ship bought with the plunder from [[Xaro Xhoan Daxos]]' manse with her long-time advisor and friend [[Jorah Mormont]] and her few remainingÂ dothraki followers.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Morghulis]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â The young ''[[Khaleesi]]''Â landed on [[Astapor]], one of the three slaver cities in the eponymous [[Slaver's Bay]], where she tookÂ Ser [[Barristan Selmy]] into her service.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Valar Dohaeris]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Sack of Astapor]]===
Looking for a way to acquire an army to take the [[Iron Throne]], Daenerys came to Astapor after Jorah Mormont told her about the prowess of the warrior-eunuchs, called the [[Unsullied]]. After witnessing their brutal training and abuse at the hands of the [[Good Masters]] and the general squalor in which the slaves of the city had to live, she resolved to free them all. She negotiated with the Masters, agreeing to trade her dragon [[Drogon]] for the command over the Unsullied and, as a gift, their translator [[Missandei]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; However, after the exchange, she ordered the Unsullied to slay the Masters and free all the slaves and commandedÂ Drogon to torch [[Kraznys mo Nakloz]], who had insulted her during her stay in the city. The Unsullied and the rampaging dragon then proceeded to [[Sack of Astapor|sack and burn the city]]. Afterwards,Â Daenerys freed her new slave soldiers, who in return pledged to serve her as free men.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â Before marching out of the city with her 8,000 Unsullied strong army, Daenerys installed a council in Astapor to rule the city in her stead.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[First of His Name]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Battle of Yunkai]]===
Although Jorah Mormont counseled Daenerys that taking [[Yunkai]] would not help her take the Iron Throne, she decided to proceed with a campaign to free all the slaves in the city and cleanse all of Slaver's Bay of slavery. Therefore, her newfound army, with [[Grey Worm]] elected as their commander&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Kissed by Fire]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;, marched on the Yellow City.

Near the city, she received the envoy [[Razdal mo Eraz]], of the [[Wise Masters]] of Yunkai. She spurned his offer of gold and ships to guide her to [[Westeros]] in exchange for leaving them alone in their business, although she kept their gold.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Bear and the Maiden Fair (episode)|The Bear and the Maiden Fair]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; After finding out that Yunkai had employed a mercenary company called the [[Second Sons]] to stand against her Unsullied, she met with the captains and tried to persuade them to her cause, to no avail. Sensing an opportunity and smitten with the beauty of Daenerys, one of the captains,Â [[Daario Naharis]], killed his colleagues and pledged his company to Daenerys' cause.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Second Sons (episode)|Second Sons]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; With Daario's insider knowledge, a small party of supporters, composed of Jorah Mormont,Â Grey Worm and himself, enteredÂ Yunkai through a back-gate to open the front-gates for her army. With the numerical advantage on their side, [[Battle of Yunkai|Yunkai fell within hours]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Rains of Castamere (episode)|The Rains of Castamere]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; The city then surrendered their slaves to Daenerys, who praised her as their 'Mother'.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Mhysa]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Siege of Meereen]]===
While on the march for [[Meereen]], the last and greatest of the slave-cities, Daenerys' army, now numbering over 10,000 and armed with siege engines, came across a series of 163 crucified slave-children pointing towards the city, one for each mile between them and Meereen.Â DaenerysÂ was greatly angered by this provocation by the [[Great Masters]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Two Swords]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

After her arrival before the city gates, Meereen sent forth a champion to challenge her best fighter in single combat. Daario Naharis swiftly dispatched the champion and Daenerys ordered the broken slave-collars from the slaves of Astapor and Yunkai be flung over the city-walls as a message to the slaves inside the city.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Breaker of Chains]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â Dâ&euro;&lsaquo;uring the night, Grey WormÂ sneaked himself and a select group of the Unsullied soldiers under his command into Meereen through the sewers,Â disguised as slaves, to arm the Meereene slaves and incite them to revolt against their Masters. In the following revolt many Masters were mobbed in the streets and the victorious slaves [[Siege of Meereen|opened the gates for Daenerys]]. Her first act was retribution for the dead slave-children: 163 Great Masters were crucified along the streets of Meereen, while Daenerys took residence in the Great Pyramid.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===Rule over Meereen===
Although the Second Sons took hold of the Meereenese navy,Â Daenerys learned that the [[Astapori ruling council|council]] she had left behind to rule Astapor had been overthrown by a self-proclaimed EmperorÂ called [[Cleon]]Â and that the Wise Masters of Yunkai had returned to power and enslaved all the freedmen in the city. Therefore, insteadÂ of marching to King's Landing in her newly acquired fleet andÂ take the Iron Throne with her army,Â Daenerys decided to remain in MeereenÂ to rule over Slaver's Bay and enforce her abolition of slavery.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[First of His Name]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â In order to accomplish this, sheÂ sent to Yunkai a Great Master at her service,Â [[Hizdahr zo Loraq]], in orderÂ to negotiate with the Wise Masters. If they did not comply with her demands of abandoning slavery once and for all, Daario would send in his Second Sons and execute them all.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Mockingbird]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Then,Â Daenerys suffered three great subsequent losses for her cause. Firstly, after [[Tywin Lannister]] uncovered her adviser Jorah MormontÂ as a former spy for King's Landing&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Laws of Gods and Men]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;, she was forced to exile him.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Mountain and the Viper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â Secondly, having been shown that her abolition of slavery had left many former servants in an even more precarious position, she begrudgingly accepted the creation of one-year contracts, effectively reintroducing slavery in all but name. Lastly, when DrogonÂ killed the [[Zalla|daughter]] of a [[Goatherd (The Children)|local goatherd]] and then disappeared, she decided to lock up her remaining two dragons in the catacombs.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
